    {
      "id": "9e971e91-16ba-40fc-912a-2e97a1e360c4",
      "type": "description",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Pour tout $k \\in \\N$, on pose \n$$X_k = \\left(\\frac{2}{1+k} , 1+e^{-k} \\right) \\in \\R^2$$",
        "html": "<p>Pour tout <span class=\"math inline\">\\(k \\in \\N\\)</span>, on pose\n<span class=\"math display\">\\[X_k = \\left(\\frac{2}{1+k} , 1+e^{-k}\n\\right) \\in \\R^2\\]</span></p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "d5f8c898-7abe-4b8e-837b-76d2b42bb990",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Soit $\\ell = (0,1)$. Calculer $||X_k-\\ell||_{2}$ où $||.||_{2}$ est la norme euclidienne.",
        "html": "<p>Soit <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\ell = (0,1)\\)</span>. Calculer\n<span class=\"math inline\">\\(||X_k-\\ell||_{2}\\)</span> où <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(||.||_{2}\\)</span> est la norme euclidienne.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "9367c1ce-4c36-42b7-a23e-3baaf0a86a3c",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$||X_k-\\ell||_{2} = \\sqrt{\\left(\\frac{2}{1+k}\\right)^2 + \\left(e^{-k}\\right)^2} = \\sqrt{\\frac{4}{(1+k)^2} + e^{-2k} }$",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(||X_k-\\ell||_{2} =\n\\sqrt{\\left(\\frac{2}{1+k}\\right)^2 + \\left(e^{-k}\\right)^2} =\n\\sqrt{\\frac{4}{(1+k)^2} + e^{-2k} }\\)</span></p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "4cd7c29b-0eb1-4447-97f1-cf5817c0a52a",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "En déduire la convergence de la suite $(X_k)$ dans $\\R^2$.",
        "html": "<p>En déduire la convergence de la suite <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\((X_k)\\)</span> dans <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(\\R^2\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
